 stack that does not tie up cpu_resources with its 1 hour (3600,000)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Lr#D0)!ep4/b^/lQBn))"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="1jwP,Wx3!oss,!gE2kpd"><field name="TEXT">Also the 'if(false)' mini-stacks will be skipped by cpu, for further non-resource burdening</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="+9h3gxi#2%NuGE`,vC#l"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="ug*I:EF9$3Ie|@}nu69/"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="b%;XCBd=jop/4hC,Z}$s"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="hbM^B$V,,P@ev3rV|%)4"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Very Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="WO#!Js]u`^j6)14a4/?y"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="R28Z:lG,fg)gczwxGOVm"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="#d0;O=]#C+}nFc2W9y6#"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=";[mCKf]/,YC#T[3)p/nv"><field name="TEXT">Levels 1, 2, 2.1</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="wH?xhw%?!)+H@8K(`%Cj"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="}4Z87=w%~gJ^_Eke2h%4"><field name="TEXT">* Level 1: Hardcoded Static via Actual_Numbers for MotorPower%</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="pM%ncz;DjH)M}Jg*ily,"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="/?7lzE5x!B-chK_NU6b9"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2: Softcoded Dynamic via Variables/Constants for MotorPower% </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id=":=y+{9-=rp4VD]|h3j{7"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="J5y]=J_.K|,Cz*X}M4gc"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2.1 Add Controller_Joystick * Level 2.2 Add Gear 3 (90%?)</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="e.sR-dua[z!5(+D]g/e9"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=",@9FZLS?C_4:za4J~fJI"><field name="TEXT">Basic Comment_Colors Usage:: Black: Very Big Picture, Blue: Big Picture, Green: Following Block_Code Moddable, Orange: Question/TODO, Magenta: Special Multi-Purpose </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="lY4R3|IdKnPo?3L(9d{h"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="YqxBbAIoCp{b{r7?@Ss/"><field name="TEXT">micro:bit Ver2 Warning during Download is Ignorable Yet Courteously Helpful</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="-)fT}I#~M+v5}*:m4p`l"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="JiTea2#Bkr3+$V#$TBJ)"><field name="TEXT">'if_then' mini-stacks useful for modular 3-D code select/duplicate/move/delete</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Y%Ht$w:E6Mm9Td?%/vl1"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="w/-dFv29qPnbK+dB}L%L"><field name="TEXT">Light_Gray Functions non-editable (backend staff-use code only)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="6TrZ{[[MgkPayXf;JhZh"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=",;mQl]{62F(*i4SNR_f6"><field name="TEXT">For Group_CHannel_# (Bot_Id): Propose: 1-10 Staff Use, 11-99 Student Use</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Iu%osd6o5ERqt9oe3*b;"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="U[y4*2_pOmX(]_4SNiFk"><field name="TEXT">SW Reset: Long_Press Logo for 3 sec min</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="1]O#A*L4j#Z}K7lF6Hkt"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="qmNXb8eCmEA2ECuIIhe6"><field name="TEXT">Built-in Diagnostic Test: Short_Press Logo for 1 sec max</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="bbKMq[P~Fm_c1g.gCj.E"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="Zsq4}%[j~@P_seEV)J^r"><field name="TEXT">'Blocks' Window homes 'on start'_stack as top_left corner of editor_screen, until 'on start' is moved below, then next stack to right presides</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="G+K},N1B{JOWG`08Ts0$"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="0BF-iXIs*K(15E++~YMv"><field name="TEXT">All These Levels are Intermediate Level Coding due to Networking Pairing Involved.  Basic Diagnostic Servo_Motors (Autonomoous) is Beginner Level.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="~svr(;CmQpbh@/.5AqP+"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="=(a`6=|WT^%Q`R,sG^!d"><field name="TEXT">This Intermediate Level Network_Pairing has 1sec_Lag Response Time; The Other Advanced Level Network_Pairing has Real_Time Response Time.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="fBgKOt?hY,s|Nyn5xP?C"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="L+)VL[0~v=AA3J(/3/pm"><field name="TEXT">For Level 1, can keep 'Forward: set manual_servo_motors' Block functional, yet reset to 0 all other 'set manual_servo_motors' Blocks for Discovery Learning</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="zzurR/%~9B[OWiN[l;tD"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="XEO[^x{hCSySPhVOhXNq"><field name="TEXT">If duplicate stacks exist, then the highest stack is active and others are non_active</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="controls_if" id="S`d8kz-bWX$=xz+H@7%G"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="V_%JKH%OJG~dIOAHM!di"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="rA3o{VWgpk(d7t{,by]#"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="|1cne(2nbICA}JjUTUX0"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="dxBRyg*O0{Y^=x_y:dLM"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="ueZ~h56No*$OAmzby@-H"><field name="TEXT">Upon open file, Editor zooms in on closest stack to right of original_origin from project_creation</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="+t)oURh[[#(isjGYx+Bl"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="(1CtZ1aXzYAV9c{(lscK"><field name="TEXT">Semantic Naming prefers '_' vs. '-' since latter can be conufused with minus_sign</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="uam(d[ls$8Uhan?BE-oq"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="Zfd-an([9^QLh#8A2-Y]"><field name="TEXT">'every 360000 ms' (1 hour) Stacks can be ignored, esp w/ 'if false' embedded</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="!mheJvUBjL@8OMi*yh$;"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="m3O13lpA*]DqI^h(icd5"><field name="TEXT">Avoid using 'show leds' Block since will cause lag &amp; degrade real-time response</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="*+g[zgqI!|0f5v3C$;=Y"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="j]akS%6JP1Ia5o2O:l.Z"><field name="TEXT">Seems like 'signficant' changes to JavaScript can activate 'format code', rearrange stacks to original position</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id=".j_RPA,93nlv!nt=22rm"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="%Z@r=WG5kBAFKP?wLXN;"><field name="TEXT">Important 'system' variables are 1) _system_Hw_DeviceType__* (Hw=Hardware) and 2) _system_Sw_ModeState__* (Sw=Software)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Zdgm8fYp03F24jmRd3sL"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="IfQWP),74VF:OD=I$d1Q"><field name="TEXT">If Buttons C-F for Gears/Misc, Maybe 'Logo Up/Down' for 'Servo_Arm Up/Down'</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="IR7--^kv.s7HPopodkvu"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="rj-^Jm5GZpL%Tw-u3/g6"><field name="TEXT">'Rotatedisplay' could be used on Bot's Led_Screen, but causes light flickering on bottom row, so maybe avoid</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="y/a}OqG5~`(7BupiwvTw"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="lYh:1$T$NHT7;x5guBC("><field name="TEXT">Reliable/Faster Response If Screen_Led_Graphics After Important Action Blocks Above</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="C5r0;1v~LfZRaOX|rV_z"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="pQp+)VMY;z*:Tf(pdO`K"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="in4#zJG#U-{?XLG$d]|?"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="u;X7Ef[0To]D;O3I1@2*"><field name="TEXT">Main upgrade from Lv1 to Lv2 is replacing cpu_laggy 'show leds' block with cpu_fast 'plox x _ y _' block, such as below: </field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="|IYZ$Zd`sxHAHY=^p_iU"><mutation elseif="4" else="1"></mutation><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="1(#gQhPKn)KS5,~!/aCP"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></sh